			<div class='post_body'>
				<p class='posted_info desc lighter ipsType_small'>
					Posted <abbr class="published" itemprop="commentTime" title="2013-02-10T16:17:54+00:00">10 February 2013 - 11:17 AM</abbr>
					
				</p>
				
				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					Since the menu uses the <a href='http://mikehillyer.com/articles/managing-hierarchical-data-in-mysql/' class='bbc_url' title='External link' rel='external'>nested set model</a> it&#39;s relatively easy to query for the parents of a menu item.<br /><br />Something like this would probably do:<br /><pre class='prettyprint lang-auto linenums:0'>
SELECT
	m.MenuId, m.Name, p.MenuId, p.Name
FROM users u
INNER JOIN groups g ON u.GroupId=g.GroupId
INNER JOIN group_menu_items gm ON gm.GroupId=g.GroupId 
INNER JOIN menu m ON gm.MenuId=m.MenuId
LEFT JOIN menu p ON m.lft BETWEEN p.lft AND p.rgt
WHERE
	u.UserId=1
</pre><br />You&#39;d probably need to do a little processing of the results within PHP to get them in whatever format the menu system&#39;s render function needs.<br />
					
					<br />
					
				</div>
				
				
